{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_ah81pil8rv9zwbj8vuw3sb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"541824496","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/private/tmp/tokenwarden-bench/claude-code/2026-07-21T17-57-52-415Z/rtk-docs-from-code-1/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md","content":"# Cache API\n\nA simple in-memory cache implementation that provides key-value storage using a `Map` under the hood.\n\n## createCache()\n\nCreates and returns a new cache instance with basic CRUD operations.\n\n```javascript\nimport { createCache } from './cache'\n\nconst cache = createCache()\n```\n\nReturns an object with the following methods for managing cached values.\n\n## Methods\n\n### get(key)\n\nRetrieves the value associated with the given key. Returns `undefined` if the key does not exist.\n\n```javascript\nconst value = cache.get('my-key')\n```\n\n### set(key, value)\n\nStores a value under the specified key. Returns the value that was set.\n\n```javascript\nconst result = cache.set('my-key', 'my-value')\n// result === 'my-value'\n```\n\n### delete(key)\n\nRemoves the value associated with the given key. Returns `true` if the key existed and was deleted, `false` otherwise.\n\n```javascript\nconst exists = cache.delete('my-key')\n```\n\n### clear()\n\nRemoves all entries from the cache.\n\n```javascript\ncache.clear()\n```\n\n---\n\n**Implementation notes:**\n- Source: `bench-targets/docs/src/cache.mjs`\n- Uses JavaScript `Map` for efficient key-value storage\n- No expiration, TTL, or maximum size limits\n"}}],"model":"qwen/qwen3.5-9b","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5517,"output_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":5496},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"63a4a154-7b5c-4755-9f63-aae8eca4cfd3","uuid":"d00d4402-0aad-440b-a273-8834adbb29ff","timestamp":"2026-07-21T20:49:59.487Z"}
